body.body: A new version of instrument hardware has been introduced for the above models. The new instrument hardware version has dedicated calibrations that are not compatible with previous versions of the instrument hardware.
, part number based instrument calibrations are released as detailed below. Dealers are requested to download the correct instrument calibration for the instrument hardware version fitted.
Use with instrument base part numbers 2508410, 2508418 and 2508427. North America and Canada markets only. Connectivity Module ready.

Manual/Visual Identification of the Instrument Hardware Version
The instrument part number can be read from the instruments as follows:
From the Instrument Build Data screen provided in the Instrument Diagnostics area of the diagnostic tool.

body.body: On a bar code label located on the back of the instrument unit. The instruments must be removed from the motorcycle to access this. The Triumph Base Part Number is provided in the first 7 numerical digits provided below the bar code.
